Hi Marta,

That?s good to know that nothing is awry as far as versions go. 

There is no active web hook once a package is accepted, the web hook is for building and checking while the package is going through the submission process. 

Once it is accepted into Bioconductor, we just have the package registered on the build machines so that the developers and core team can check if it builds successfully on the devel and RELEASE branches. 

Best,

Nitesh 


